2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE BILL NO. 429
BY SENATOR LAMBERT
1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact R.S. 34:851.20(C), relative to boat registration; to provide for the
3 issuance of certificates of number and decal for certain boats; to provide for
4 applications and required documentation; and to provide for related matters.
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
6 Section 1. R.S. 34:851.20(C) is hereby amended and reenacted to read as follows:
7 §851.20. Identification number
8 * * *
9 C.(1) Should the ownership of a motorboat, houseboat, or sailboat change,
10 a new application form with a five dollar fee shall be filed with the commission,
11 along with the registration fee required by this Section, and a new certificate of
12 number and a decal, valid for three years, shall be awarded in the same manner as
13 provided for in an original award of number.
14 (2)(a) An application for a certificate of number may be filed by the
15 possessor of a motorboat, houseboat, or sailboat with a certificate of number
16 that has lapsed for at least five years. The possessor shall submit an affidavit
17 stating the following:
18 (i) Notice of the application has been provided by certified mail, return
19 receipt requested, to the last holder of a certificate of number.
20 (ii) The applicant has been in possession of the boat for at least one year
21 immediately preceding the date of application.
22 (b) Copies of the notice and return receipt shall be submitted to the
23 commission with the affidavit.
